pma:database.name: phd
pma:database.pma:table: CREATE TABLE `courses` ( `cid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `timestamp` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, `sregno` int(20) NOT NULL, `cname` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `coordinator` varchar(400) NOT NULL, `credits` float NOT NULL, `L` float NOT NULL, `T` float NOT NULL, `P` float NOT NULL, `semcode` varchar(10) NOT NULL, `department` varchar(4) NOT NULL, `class` varchar(10) NOT NULL, `grade` varchar(4) DEFAULT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`cid`), UNIQUE KEY `sregno` (`sregno`,`cname`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=4 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `faculty` ( `fid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `department` varchar(4) NOT NULL, `fname` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `email` varchar(50) NOT NULL, `designation` varchar(300) NOT NULL, `r_int` varchar(200) NOT NULL, `url` varchar(200) NOT NULL, `dob` date NOT NULL, `phone` varchar(20) NOT NULL, `faculty_code` varchar(4) NOT NULL, `def` int(11) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1', PRIMARY KEY (`fid`), UNIQUE KEY `faculty_code` (`faculty_code`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=60 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `login` ( `sno` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `role` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `_id` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL, `password` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `full_name` varchar(200) NOT NULL, `phone` varchar(20) NOT NULL, `email` varchar(300) NOT NULL, `photo` int(11) NOT NULL DEFAULT '0', PRIMARY KEY (`sno`), UNIQUE KEY `_id` (`_id`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=28 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `progress` ( `timestamp` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, `sno` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `sid` int(11) NOT NULL, `urbdate` date DEFAULT NULL, `percentage` int(11) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`sno`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=122 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `research_book` ( `rid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `chapter_title` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `authors` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `publisher` varchar(600) NOT NULL, `page_numbers` varchar(10) NOT NULL, `book_publish_year` int(5) NOT NULL, `book_isbn` int(14) NOT NULL, `sid` int(11) NOT NULL, `status` varchar(100) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`rid`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=2 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `research_conference` ( `rid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `title` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `people` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `conference_name` varchar(300) NOT NULL, `conference_date` date NOT NULL, `conference_location` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `status` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `sid` int(11) NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`rid`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=3 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `research_journal` ( `rid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `title` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `authors` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `journal_name` varchar(300) NOT NULL, `journal_volume` int(11) NOT NULL, `journal_no` int(11) NOT NULL, `publish_date` date NOT NULL, `journal_pages` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `status` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `sid` int(11) NOT NULL, `journal_impact` double NOT NULL, PRIMARY KEY (`rid`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=2 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;

CREATE TABLE `student` ( `sid` int(11) NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT, `timestamp` timestamp NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, `regno` int(11) NOT NULL, `sname` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `full_part` varchar(5) NOT NULL, `status` varchar(300) NOT NULL, `sdob` date NOT NULL, `semail` varchar(100) NOT NULL, `sbranch` varchar(4) DEFAULT NULL, `sdoa` date NOT NULL, `sdurb` date NOT NULL, `sthesis` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `sphone` varchar(200) NOT NULL, `chair` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `supervisor1` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `supervisor2` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `cognate1` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `cognate2` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `outside` varchar(500) NOT NULL, `def` int(11) NOT NULL DEFAULT '1', PRIMARY KEY (`sid`), UNIQUE KEY `regno` (`regno`) ) ENGINE=InnoDB AUTO_INCREMENT=91 DEFAULT CHARSET=latin1;
